BY virtue of the King's commission of the peace, oyer and terminer and gaol delivery of Newgate, holden for the city of London and county of Middlesex, at
Justice-hall in the Old Bailey, before the
Right Honourable Sir Samuel Fludyer, Bart. Lord Mayor ;
Sir William Moreton, Recorder ;
James Eyre, Esq; deputy Recorder , and others of his Majesty's Justices of oyer and terminer of the city of London, and Justices of gaol delivery of Newgate, holden for the said city and county of Middlesex on Wednesday the 15th, Thursday the 16th, Friday the 17th, and Saturday the 18th of September, 1762, in the second year of his Majesty's reign, three prisoners were capitally convicted and received sentence of death.
